"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-08-09-morocco-outclass-egypt-take-olympic-mens-football-bronze\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"NANTES, France (AFP) - The prolific Soufiane Rahimi scored twice and Captain Achraf Hakimi netted a stunning free kick as Morocco hammered Egypt 6-0 on Thursday to take Olympic men's football bronze.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 199, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8, \"end\": 14, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.999999993764277, \"rank\": 6.23554297326892e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 36, \"end\": 51, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soufiane_Rahimi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Soufiane Rahimi\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soufiane_Rahimi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soufiane_Rahimi\"}, {\"begin\": 77, \"end\": 90, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achraf_Hakimi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Achraf Hakimi\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achraf_Hakimi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achraf_Hakimi\"}, {\"begin\": 122, \"end\": 129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.192757161446218e-20, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 139, \"end\": 144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4662557744245396e-16, \"text\": \"Egypt\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rahimi's brace took him to eight goals at the Olympics, cementing his status as the tournament's top scorer, while Abde Ezzalzouli, Bilal El Khannouss and Akram Nakach also scored in a comprehensive win at the Stade de la Beaujoire in Nantes.\", \"from\": 201, \"to\": 443, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 316, \"end\": 331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abde_Ezzalzouli\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Abde Ezzalzouli\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abde_Ezzalzouli\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abde_Ezzalzouli\"}, {\"begin\": 333, \"end\": 338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bilal_ibn_Rabah\", \"score\": 0.9998787555099973, \"rank\": 0.00012125917753539995, \"text\": \"Bilal\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bilal_ibn_Rabah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bilal_ibn_Rabah\"}, {\"begin\": 436, \"end\": 442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FC_Nantes\", \"score\": 0.9999999999295142, \"rank\": 7.053998413805576e-11, \"text\": \"Nantes\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FC_Nantes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FC_Nantes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hakimi's late strike put the icing on the cake as Morocco claimed a first Olympic football medal, and a first for North Africa.\", \"from\": 445, \"to\": 572, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 495, \"end\": 502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.192757161446218e-20, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 559, \"end\": 571, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9998052850749847, \"rank\": 0.0001935352453352969, \"text\": \"North Africa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Morocco, who beat Argentina in their opening group game and were eventually beaten by Spain in the semi-finals, had already defeated Egypt in the final of last year's Under-23 Africa Cup of Nations.\", \"from\": 574, \"to\": 772, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 574, \"end\": 581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.192757161446218e-20, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 592, \"end\": 601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999997349196188, \"rank\": 1.6284041135193894e-07, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 660, \"end\": 665, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.4218938760462165e-16, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 707, \"end\": 712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4662557744245396e-16, \"text\": \"Egypt\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That success was what allowed them to qualify for the Olympics, and they secured a medal in rampant fashion with Ezzalzouli, of Real Betis in Spain, putting Morocco ahead from a superb strike just inside the box midway through the first half.\", \"from\": 774, \"to\": 1016, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 916, \"end\": 921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.4218938760462165e-16, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 931, \"end\": 938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.192757161446218e-20, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rahimi made it 2-0 shortly after when he headed in a cross by Ezzalzouli, before the Atlas Lions ran away with the game in the second half.\", \"from\": 1018, \"to\": 1157, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1103, \"end\": 1114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.267956818269779e-26, \"text\": \"Atlas Lions\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"El Khannouss curled a low shot into the bottom-right corner from just outside the box for the third goal, and Rahimi got his second to make it 4-0 when he controlled a pass by Ilias Akhomach before firing in.\", \"from\": 1159, \"to\": 1367, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Striker Rahimi, who has at least four more goals than any other player in the tournament, then turned provider for defender Akram Nakach to make it five.\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1522, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1369, \"end\": 1376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FV102_Striker\", \"score\": 0.9914626353042418, \"rank\": 0.008378873383159107, \"text\": \"Striker\", \"types\": [\"Q728\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FV102_Striker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FV102_Striker\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Hakimi saved the best for last by finding the net with a missile of a free kick from 30 metres three minutes from the end.\", \"from\": 1524, \"to\": 1655, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That was Morocco's 17th goal in six matches at the Games.\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1713, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1665, \"end\": 1672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.192757161446218e-20, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hosts France play Spain in the gold medal match in Paris on Friday.\", \"from\": 1715, \"to\": 1782, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1721, \"end\": 1727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.999999993764277, \"rank\": 6.23554297326892e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1733, \"end\": 1738, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.4218938760462165e-16, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1766, \"end\": 1771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999994736299, \"rank\": 5.263531955828517e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"HOUSE RULES\", \"from\": 1786, \"to\": 1797, \"entities\": []}]}"